40
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:21,867
I am sorry you had to see that.
She is always so very angry.

41
00:05:21,867 --> 00:05:24,133
Anybody who lose parent...

42
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,467
....have much grief.

43
00:05:28,467 --> 00:05:32,467
Grief trapped in the heart
become big anger.

44
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:35,333
I don't know what to do anymore.

45
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:37,333
Have suggestion.

46
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:49,533
Suggest Louisa-san...

47
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:51,800
....water flowers.

48
00:05:53,533 --> 00:05:55,600
What do you mean, flowers?

49
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:58,067
Not here flower.

50
00:05:58,067 --> 00:06:01,733
Flower in Miyagi garden.
California.

51
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,067
Hi, Angel.

52
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:56,683
Hi.

53
00:07:01,467 --> 00:07:03,600
How you doing, huh?

54
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:08,400
How's your wing?
Does it feel any better?

55
00:07:09,533 --> 00:07:12,800
Come here. Can you come to me?
Come here, hop to my hand.

56
00:07:13,867 --> 00:07:17,133
Good girl.
Let's go for a walk, okay?

57
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:18,733
Come on.

58
00:07:21,133 --> 00:07:24,333
I got in another argument
with my grandmother tonight.

59
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:27,667
I wish my parents were still here.

60
00:07:29,667 --> 00:07:32,267
Everything wouldn't be
so messed up.

61
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,000
You know...

62
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,933
if they found out you were here,
they'd take you away.

63
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:46,133
Wouldn't that be awful?
In some small cage.

64
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:48,133
You wouldn't know anybody.

65
00:07:55,467 --> 00:07:58,933
<i>- 544, handle code two.
- We're checking it out.</i>

66
00:08:00,267 --> 00:08:03,733
Larry, look at that,
up on the roof.

67
00:08:07,667 --> 00:08:10,133
If she hasn't jumped yet,
I am going to throw her.

68
00:08:10,133 --> 00:08:12,533
I will be back.
You be quiet, okay?

69
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,133
You be quiet.

70
00:08:20,267 --> 00:08:23,067
- You all right?
- Yeah, I am fine.

71
00:08:29,067 --> 00:08:32,067
- You think she's still up here?
- Beats me.

72
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,267
- What was that?
- Look out!

73
00:08:36,867 --> 00:08:39,133
You! Hold it right there!

74
00:08:39,133 --> 00:08:41,533
I said hold it!
Police!

75
00:08:58,467 --> 00:08:59,717
Stop!

76
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,600
Oh, come on!

77
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,267
Look, I have heard all this before.

78
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:22,733
Why don't you put it on a video so I can
fast-forward through the familiar parts?

79
00:09:22,733 --> 00:09:27,067
I love you, Julie,
and I know you love me.

80
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:30,933
But these days,
we act as if we hate each other.

81
00:09:30,933 --> 00:09:35,133
Talking doesn't seem to help.
It just makes things worse.

82
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:39,400
Mr. Miyagi's invited me to spend
some time at his house in California.

83
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:42,600
He will stay here and take care of
everything while I am gone.

84
